import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int total = sc.nextInt();
            if (total == 0) break;

            int sum = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
                sum += sc.nextInt();
            }

            System.out.println(total - sum);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        String target = sc.nextLine();
        int n = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine());

        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            String ring = sc.nextLine();
            String doubled = ring + ring;

            if (doubled.contains(target)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();
            int b = sc.nextInt();

            int distFromEdge = Math.min(Math.min(a - 1, N - a), Math.min(b - 1, N - b));

            int color = (distFromEdge % 3) + 1;

            System.out.println(color);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00483_3P.java: 1-56 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int M = sc.nextInt();
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        char[][] grid = new char[M][N];
        for (int i = 0; i < M; i++) {
            String line = sc.next();
            for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
                grid[i][j] = line.charAt(j);
            }
        }

        int[][][] prefix = new int[3][M + 1][N + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= M; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= N; j++) {
                char terrain = grid[i-1][j-1];

                for (int t = 0; t < 3; t++) {
                    prefix[t][i][j] = prefix[t][i-1][j] + prefix[t][i][j-1] - prefix[t][i-1][j-1];
                }

                if (terrain == 'J') {
                    prefix[0][i][j]++;
                } else if (terrain == 'O') {
                    prefix[1][i][j]++;
                } else if (terrain == 'I') {
                    prefix[2][i][j]++;
                }
            }
        }

        for (int q = 0; q < K; q++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();
            int b = sc.nextInt();
            int c = sc.nextInt();
            int d = sc.nextInt();

            int[] count = new int[3];
            for (int t = 0; t < 3; t++) {
                count[t] = prefix[t][c][d] - prefix[t][a-1][d] - prefix[t][c][b-1] + prefix[t][a-1][b-1];
            }

            System.out.println(count[0] + " " + count[1] + " " + count[2]);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00500_1P.java: 1-41 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] players = new int[n][3];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                players[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        for (int game = 0; game < 3; game++) {
            Map<Integer, Integer> count = new HashMap<>();

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int num = players[i][game];
                count.put(num, count.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
            }

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int num = players[i][game];
                if (count.get(num) == 1) {
                    players[i][game] = num;
                } else {
                    players[i][game] = 0;
                }
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int total = players[i][0] + players[i][1] + players[i][2];
            System.out.println(total);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00501_4P.java: 1-43 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        String target = sc.next();

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            String board = sc.next();
            if (canMakeSignboard(board, target)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }

    static boolean canMakeSignboard(String board, String target) {
        int n = board.length();
        int m = target.length();

        for (int start = 0; start < n; start++) {
            for (int interval = 1; start + (m - 1) * interval < n; interval++) {
                boolean valid = true;
                for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
                    int pos = start + i * interval;
                    if (board.charAt(pos) != target.charAt(i)) {
                        valid = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (valid) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        String target = sc.next();

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            String board = sc.next();
            if (canMakeSignboard(board, target)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }

    static boolean canMakeSignboard(String board, String target) {
        int n = board.length();
        int m = target.length();

        for (int start = 0; start < n; start++) {
            for (int interval = 1; start + (m - 1) * interval < n; interval++) {
                boolean match = true;
                for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                    int pos = start + j * interval;
                    if (board.charAt(pos) != target.charAt(j)) {
                        match = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (match) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00502_2P.java: 1-62 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int D = sc.nextInt();
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int[] T = new int[D];
        for (int i = 0; i < D; i++) {
            T[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[] A = new int[N];
        int[] B = new int[N];
        int[] C = new int[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            A[i] = sc.nextInt();
            B[i] = sc.nextInt();
            C[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        List<List<Integer>> suitable = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < D; i++) {
            suitable.add(new ArrayList<>());
            for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
                if (A[j] <= T[i] && T[i] <= B[j]) {
                    suitable.get(i).add(j);
                }
            }
        }

        int[][] dp = new int[D][N];
        for (int i = 0; i < D; i++) {
            Arrays.fill(dp[i], -1);
        }

        for (int cloth : suitable.get(0)) {
            dp[0][cloth] = 0;
        }

        for (int day = 1; day < D; day++) {
            for (int cloth : suitable.get(day)) {
                for (int prevCloth : suitable.get(day - 1)) {
                    if (dp[day - 1][prevCloth] != -1) {
                        int diff = Math.abs(C[cloth] - C[prevCloth]);
                        dp[day][cloth] = Math.max(dp[day][cloth], dp[day - 1][prevCloth] + diff);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        int result = 0;
        for (int cloth : suitable.get(D - 1)) {
            result = Math.max(result, dp[D - 1][cloth]);
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }
}

public class Main {

        int D = sc.nextInt();
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int[] T = new int[D];
        for (int i = 0; i < D; i++) {
            T[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[] A = new int[N];
        int[] B = new int[N];
        int[] C = new int[N];

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            A[i] = sc.nextInt();
            B[i] = sc.nextInt();
            C[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        List<List<Integer>> suitable = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int day = 0; day < D; day++) {
            suitable.add(new ArrayList<>());
            for (int cloth = 0; cloth < N; cloth++) {
                if (A[cloth] <= T[day] && T[day] <= B[cloth]) {
                    suitable.get(day).add(cloth);
                }
            }
        }

        int[][] dp = new int[D][N];
        for (int i = 0; i < D; i++) {
            Arrays.fill(dp[i], -1);
        }

        for (int cloth : suitable.get(0)) {
            dp[0][cloth] = 0;
        }

        for (int day = 1; day < D; day++) {
            for (int cloth : suitable.get(day)) {
                for (int prevCloth : suitable.get(day - 1)) {
                    if (dp[day - 1][prevCloth] != -1) {
                        int diff = Math.abs(C[cloth] - C[prevCloth]);
                        dp[day][cloth] = Math.max(dp[day][cloth], dp[day - 1][prevCloth] + diff);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        int result = 0;
        for (int cloth : suitable.get(D - 1)) {
            result = Math.max(result, dp[D - 1][cloth]);
        }

        System.out.println(result);

train/1/claude_p00512_0P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        Map<String, Integer> orders = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            String product = sc.next();
            int quantity = sc.nextInt();
            orders.put(product, orders.getOrDefault(product, 0) + quantity);
        }

        List<String> products = new ArrayList<>(orders.keySet());

        products.sort((a, b) -> {
            if (a.length() != b.length()) {
                return a.length() - b.length();
            }
            return a.compareTo(b);
        });

        for (String product : products) {
            System.out.println(product + " " + orders.get(product));
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00516_2P.java: 1-41 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int M = sc.nextInt();

        int[] A = new int[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            A[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[] votes = new int[N];

        for (int j = 0; j < M; j++) {
            int B = sc.nextInt();

            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                if (A[i] <= B) {
                    votes[i]++;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        int maxVotes = 0;
        int winnerSport = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            if (votes[i] > maxVotes) {
                maxVotes = votes[i];
                winnerSport = i + 1;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(winnerSport);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Vote {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int M = sc.nextInt();

        int[] A = new int[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            A[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[] votes = new int[N];

        for (int j = 0; j < M; j++) {
            int B = sc.nextInt();

            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                if (A[i] <= B) {
                    votes[i]++;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        int maxVotes = 0;
        int winner = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            if (votes[i] > maxVotes) {
                maxVotes = votes[i];
                winner = i + 1;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(winner);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00517_4P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int W = sc.nextInt();
        int H = sc.nextInt();
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int totalDistance = 0;
        int prevX = sc.nextInt();
        int prevY = sc.nextInt();

        for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
            int currX = sc.nextInt();
            int currY = sc.nextInt();

            int dx = Math.abs(currX - prevX);
            int dy = Math.abs(currY - prevY);

            totalDistance += Math.max(dx, dy);

            prevX = currX;
            prevY = currY;
        }

        System.out.println(totalDistance);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int A = sc.nextInt();
        int B = sc.nextInt();
        int C = sc.nextInt();
        int D = sc.nextInt();
        int E = sc.nextInt();
        int F = sc.nextInt();

        int[] sciences = {A, B, C, D};
        Arrays.sort(sciences);
        int scienceSum = sciences[3] + sciences[2] + sciences[1];

        int socialSum = Math.max(E, F);

        System.out.println(scienceSum + socialSum);
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00595_0P.java: 1-30 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (scanner.hasNextLine()) {
            String line = scanner.nextLine().trim();
            if (line.isEmpty()) break;

            String[] parts = line.split("\\s+");
            int a = Integer.parseInt(parts[0]);
            int b = Integer.parseInt(parts[1]);

            System.out.println(gcd(a, b));
        }

        scanner.close();
    }

    private static int gcd(int a, int b) {
        while (b != 0) {
            int temp = b;
            b = a % b;
            a = temp;
        }
        return a;
    }
}

import java.util.*;
import java.io.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));
        String line;

        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
            int n = Integer.parseInt(line.trim());
            if (n == 0) continue;

            int[] times = new int[n];
            String[] parts = br.readLine().trim().split("\\s+");
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                times[i] = Integer.parseInt(parts[i]);
            }

            Arrays.sort(times);

            long penalty = 0;
            long currentTime = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                currentTime += times[i];
                penalty += currentTime;
            }

            System.out.println(penalty);
        }
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00605_1P.java: 1-48 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int N = scanner.nextInt();
            int K = scanner.nextInt();

            if (N == 0 && K == 0) {
                break;
            }

            int[] available = new int[K];
            for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
                available[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            }

            int[][] requirements = new int[N][K];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                    requirements[i][j] = scanner.nextInt();
                }
            }

            int[] totalNeeded = new int[K];
            for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                    totalNeeded[j] += requirements[i][j];
                }
            }

            boolean possible = true;
            for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                if (totalNeeded[j] > available[j]) {
                    possible = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            System.out.println(possible ? "Yes" : "No");
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int N = sc.nextInt();
            int K = sc.nextInt();

            if (N == 0 && K == 0) {
                break;
            }

            int[] stock = new int[K];
            for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
                stock[i] = sc.nextInt();
            }

            int[][] needs = new int[N][K];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                    needs[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
                }
            }

            int[] totalNeeded = new int[K];
            for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                    totalNeeded[j] += needs[i][j];
                }
            }

            boolean possible = true;
            for (int j = 0; j < K; j++) {
                if (totalNeeded[j] > stock[j]) {
                    possible = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            System.out.println(possible ? "Yes" : "No");
        }

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int m = sc.nextInt();

        for (int test = 0; test < m; test++) {
            int[][] grid = new int[5][5];
            for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
                    grid[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
                }
            }

            int maxArea = 0;

            for (int r1 = 0; r1 < 5; r1++) {
                for (int c1 = 0; c1 < 5; c1++) {
                    for (int r2 = r1; r2 < 5; r2++) {
                        for (int c2 = c1; c2 < 5; c2++) {
                            boolean valid = true;
                            int area = 0;

                            for (int i = r1; i <= r2 && valid; i++) {
                                for (int j = c1; j <= c2 && valid; j++) {
                                    if (grid[i][j] == 0) {
                                        valid = false;
                                    } else {
                                        area++;
                                    }
                                }
                            }

                            if (valid) {
                                maxArea = Math.max(maxArea, area);
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxArea);
        }
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00700_4P.java: 1-35 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        for (int cave = 0; cave < N; cave++) {
            int x = 0, y = 0;
            int maxDist = 0;
            int treasureX = 0, treasureY = 0;

            while (true) {
                int dx = sc.nextInt();
                int dy = sc.nextInt();

                if (dx == 0 && dy == 0) break;

                x += dx;
                y += dy;

                int distSq = x * x + y * y;

                if (distSq > maxDist || (distSq == maxDist && x > treasureX)) {
                    maxDist = distSq;
                    treasureX = x;
                    treasureY = y;
                }
            }

            System.out.println(treasureX + " " + treasureY);
        }
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int N = sc.nextInt();
            if (N == 0) break;

            int W = sc.nextInt();
            int H = sc.nextInt();

            boolean[][] field = new boolean[H + 1][W + 1];

            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                int y = sc.nextInt();
                field[y][x] = true;
            }

            int S = sc.nextInt();
            int T = sc.nextInt();

            int maxTrees = 0;

            for (int startY = 1; startY <= H - T + 1; startY++) {
                for (int startX = 1; startX <= W - S + 1; startX++) {
                    int count = 0;

                    for (int y = startY; y < startY + T; y++) {
                        for (int x = startX; x < startX + S; x++) {
                            if (field[y][x]) {
                                count++;
                            }
                        }
                    }

                    maxTrees = Math.max(maxTrees, count);
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxTrees);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

Class 406:   2 fragments, nominal size 55 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p00707_4P.java: 1-71 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static int W, H;
    static char[][] matrix;
    static String maxNumber = "0";

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            W = sc.nextInt();
            H = sc.nextInt();
            if (W == 0 && H == 0) break;

            matrix = new char[H][W];
            for (int i = 0; i < H; i++) {
                String line = sc.next();
                for (int j = 0; j < W; j++) {
                    matrix[i][j] = line.charAt(j);
                }
            }

            maxNumber = "0";

            for (int i = 0; i < H; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < W; j++) {
                    if (Character.isDigit(matrix[i][j])) {
                        dfs(i, j, "");
                    }
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxNumber);
        }
    }

    static void dfs(int row, int col, String current) {
        if (row < 0 || row >= H || col < 0 || col >= W) return;
        if (!Character.isDigit(matrix[row][col])) return;

        current += matrix[row][col];

        if (isLarger(current, maxNumber)) {
            maxNumber = current;
        }

        dfs(row, col + 1, current);

        dfs(row + 1, col, current);
    }

    static boolean isLarger(String a, String b) {
        a = removeLeadingZeros(a);
        b = removeLeadingZeros(b);

        if (a.length() != b.length()) {
            return a.length() > b.length();
        }
        return a.compareTo(b) > 0;
    }

    static String removeLeadingZeros(String s) {
        int i = 0;
        while (i < s.length() - 1 && s.charAt(i) == '0') {
            i++;
        }
        return s.substring(i);
    }
}
test/1/claude_p00707_2P.java: 1-73 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static int W, H;
    static char[][] matrix;
    static String maxNumber = "0";

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            W = sc.nextInt();
            H = sc.nextInt();

            if (W == 0 && H == 0) break;

            matrix = new char[H][W];
            for (int i = 0; i < H; i++) {
                String line = sc.next();
                for (int j = 0; j < W; j++) {
                    matrix[i][j] = line.charAt(j);
                }
            }

            maxNumber = "0";

            for (int i = 0; i < H; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < W; j++) {
                    if (Character.isDigit(matrix[i][j])) {
                        dfs(i, j, "");
                    }
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxNumber);
        }
    }

    static void dfs(int row, int col, String current) {
        if (row < 0 || row >= H || col < 0 || col >= W) return;
        if (!Character.isDigit(matrix[row][col])) return;

        current += matrix[row][col];

        if (isLarger(current, maxNumber)) {
            maxNumber = current;
        }

        dfs(row, col + 1, current);

        dfs(row + 1, col, current);
    }

    static boolean isLarger(String a, String b) {
        a = removeLeadingZeros(a);
        b = removeLeadingZeros(b);

        if (a.length() != b.length()) {
            return a.length() > b.length();
        }

        return a.compareTo(b) > 0;
    }

    static String removeLeadingZeros(String s) {
        int i = 0;
        while (i < s.length() - 1 && s.charAt(i) == '0') {
            i++;
        }
        return s.substring(i);
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00723_4P.java: 1-39 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int m = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            String train = sc.nextLine();
            System.out.println(countConfigurations(train));
        }
    }

    static int countConfigurations(String train) {
        Set<String> configurations = new HashSet<>();
        int n = train.length();

        for (int split = 1; split < n; split++) {
            String left = train.substring(0, split);
            String right = train.substring(split);

            String leftReversed = new StringBuilder(left).reverse().toString();
            String rightReversed = new StringBuilder(right).reverse().toString();

            configurations.add(left + right);
            configurations.add(left + rightReversed);
            configurations.add(leftReversed + right);
            configurations.add(leftReversed + rightReversed);
            configurations.add(right + left);
            configurations.add(right + leftReversed);
            configurations.add(rightReversed + left);
            configurations.add(rightReversed + leftReversed);
        }

        return configurations.size();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            int[] scores = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                scores[i] = sc.nextInt();
            }

            Arrays.sort(scores);

            int sum = 0;
            for (int i = 1; i < n - 1; i++) {
                sum += scores[i];
            }

            int result = sum / (n - 2);
            System.out.println(result);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00729_1P.java: 1-73 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class Record {
        int time, pc, student, status;
        Record(int t, int n, int m, int s) {
            time = t; pc = n; student = m; status = s;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int N = sc.nextInt();
            int M = sc.nextInt();
            if (N == 0 && M == 0) break;

            int r = sc.nextInt();
            List<Record> records = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int i = 0; i < r; i++) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                int n = sc.nextInt();
                int m = sc.nextInt();
                int s = sc.nextInt();
                records.add(new Record(t, n, m, s));
            }

            int q = sc.nextInt();
            for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
                int ts = sc.nextInt();
                int te = sc.nextInt();
                int m = sc.nextInt();

                System.out.println(calculateUsage(records, ts, te, m));
            }
        }
    }

    static int calculateUsage(List<Record> records, int ts, int te, int student) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> loginTimes = new HashMap<>();
        int totalUsage = 0;

        for (Record rec : records) {
            if (rec.student != student) continue;

            if (rec.status == 1) {
                loginTimes.put(rec.pc, rec.time);
            } else {
                Integer loginTime = loginTimes.get(rec.pc);
                if (loginTime != null) {
                    int start = Math.max(loginTime, ts);
                    int end = Math.min(rec.time, te);
                    if (start < end) {
                        totalUsage += end - start;
                    }
                    loginTimes.remove(rec.pc);
                }
            }
        }

        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : loginTimes.entrySet()) {
            int loginTime = entry.getValue();
            int start = Math.max(loginTime, ts);
            if (start < te) {
                totalUsage += te - start;
            }
        }

        return totalUsage;
    }
}

    static int calculateUsage(List<Record> records, int ts, int te, int student) {

train/1/claude_p00734_1P.java: 1-57 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            int m = sc.nextInt();

            if (n == 0 && m == 0) break;

            int[] taro = new int[n];
            int[] hanako = new int[m];

            int taroSum = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                taro[i] = sc.nextInt();
                taroSum += taro[i];
            }

            int hanakoSum = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
                hanako[i] = sc.nextInt();
                hanakoSum += hanako[i];
            }

            int bestTaro = -1, bestHanako = -1;
            int minSum = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                    int newTaroSum = taroSum - taro[i] + hanako[j];
                    int newHanakoSum = hanakoSum - hanako[j] + taro[i];

                    if (newTaroSum == newHanakoSum) {
                        int sum = taro[i] + hanako[j];
                        if (sum < minSum) {
                            minSum = sum;
                            bestTaro = taro[i];
                            bestHanako = hanako[j];
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            if (bestTaro == -1) {
                System.out.println(-1);
            } else {
                System.out.println(bestTaro + " " + bestHanako);
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p00780_2P.java: 1-39 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int maxN = 32768;
        boolean[] isPrime = new boolean[maxN + 1];
        Arrays.fill(isPrime, true);
        isPrime[0] = isPrime[1] = false;

        for (int i = 2; i * i <= maxN; i++) {
            if (isPrime[i]) {
                for (int j = i * i; j <= maxN; j += i) {
                    isPrime[j] = false;
                }
            }
        }

        int n;
        while ((n = sc.nextInt()) != 0) {
            int count = 0;

            for (int p1 = 2; p1 <= n / 2; p1++) {
                if (isPrime[p1]) {
                    int p2 = n - p1;
                    if (isPrime[p2]) {
                        count++;
                    }
                }
            }

            System.out.println(count);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p01223_0P.java: 1-34 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();

        for (int i = 0; i < t; i++) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            int[] heights = new int[n];

            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                heights[j] = sc.nextInt();
            }

            int maxUp = 0;
            int maxDown = 0;

            for (int j = 1; j < n; j++) {
                int diff = heights[j] - heights[j-1];
                if (diff > 0) {
                    maxUp = Math.max(maxUp, diff);
                } else if (diff < 0) {
                    maxDown = Math.max(maxDown, -diff);
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxUp + " " + maxDown);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                heights[j] = sc.nextInt();
            }

            int maxUp = 0;
            int maxDown = 0;

            for (int j = 1; j < n; j++) {
                int diff = heights[j] - heights[j-1];
                if (diff > 0) {
                    maxUp = Math.max(maxUp, diff);
                } else if (diff < 0) {
                    maxDown = Math.max(maxDown, -diff);
                }
            }

            System.out.println(maxUp + " " + maxDown);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p01513_0P.java: 1-55 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int N = sc.nextInt();
            if (N == 0) break;

            List<Set<Integer>> knows = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int i = 0; i <= N; i++) {
                knows.add(new HashSet<>());
            }

            for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
                int M = sc.nextInt();
                for (int j = 0; j < M; j++) {
                    int person = sc.nextInt();
                    knows.get(i).add(person);
                }
            }

            int K = sc.nextInt();
            Set<Integer> leaked = new HashSet<>();
            for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
                leaked.add(sc.nextInt());
            }

            List<Integer> suspects = new ArrayList<>();

            for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
                boolean canLeak = true;
                for (int leakedPerson : leaked) {
                    if (!knows.get(i).contains(leakedPerson)) {
                        canLeak = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (canLeak) {
                    suspects.add(i);
                }
            }

            if (suspects.size() == 1) {
                System.out.println(suspects.get(0));
            } else {
                System.out.println(-1);
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p01751_0P.java: 1-35 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int c = sc.nextInt();

        int cycle = a + b;

        int lcm = lcm(cycle, 60);

        for (int t = 0; t * 60 <= lcm; t++) {
            int arrivalTime = 60 * t + c;
            int timeInCycle = arrivalTime % cycle;

            if (timeInCycle <= a) {
                System.out.println(arrivalTime);
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(-1);
    }

    static int gcd(int a, int b) {
        return b == 0 ? a : gcd(b, a % b);
    }

    static int lcm(int a, int b) {
        return a / gcd(a, b) * b;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p01803_4P.java: 1-70 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            String[] airports = new String[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                airports[i] = sc.next();
            }

            String[] sequences = new String[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                sequences[i] = generateSequence(airports[i]);
            }

            int result = findMinK(sequences);
            System.out.println(result);
        }

        sc.close();
    }

    private static String generateSequence(String name) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        Set<Character> vowels = Set.of('a', 'i', 'u', 'e', 'o');

        sb.append(name.charAt(0));

        for (int i = 0; i < name.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (vowels.contains(name.charAt(i))) {
                sb.append(name.charAt(i + 1));
            }
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }

    private static int findMinK(String[] sequences) {
        int maxLen = 0;
        for (String seq : sequences) {
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, seq.length());
        }

        for (int k = 1; k <= maxLen; k++) {
            Set<String> codes = new HashSet<>();
            boolean valid = true;

            for (String seq : sequences) {
                String code = seq.length() >= k ? seq.substring(0, k) : seq;
                if (codes.contains(code)) {
                    valid = false;
                    break;
                }
                codes.add(code);
            }

            if (valid) {
                return k;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
test/1/claude_p01803_3P.java: 1-70 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            String[] airports = new String[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                airports[i] = sc.next();
            }

            String[] codes = new String[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                codes[i] = generateCodeString(airports[i]);
            }

            int result = findMinK(codes);
            System.out.println(result);
        }

        sc.close();
    }

    private static String generateCodeString(String name) {
        StringBuilder code = new StringBuilder();
        Set<Character> vowels = Set.of('a', 'i', 'u', 'e', 'o');

        code.append(name.charAt(0));

        for (int i = 0; i < name.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (vowels.contains(name.charAt(i))) {
                code.append(name.charAt(i + 1));
            }
        }

        return code.toString();
    }

    private static int findMinK(String[] codes) {
        int maxLength = 0;
        for (String code : codes) {
            maxLength = Math.max(maxLength, code.length());
        }

        for (int k = 1; k <= maxLength; k++) {
            Set<String> usedCodes = new HashSet<>();
            boolean valid = true;

            for (String code : codes) {
                String truncated = code.length() >= k ? code.substring(0, k) : code;
                if (usedCodes.contains(truncated)) {
                    valid = false;
                    break;
                }
                usedCodes.add(truncated);
            }

            if (valid) {
                return k;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}

Class 420:   2 fragments, nominal size 83 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p02245_3P.java: 1-100 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static final int[][] TARGET = {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}, {7, 8, 0}};
    static final int[] dx = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
    static final int[] dy = {0, 0, -1, 1};

    static class State {
        int[][] board;
        int zeroX, zeroY;
        int steps;

        State(int[][] board, int zeroX, int zeroY, int steps) {
            this.board = new int[3][3];
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                System.arraycopy(board[i], 0, this.board[i], 0, 3);
            }
            this.zeroX = zeroX;
            this.zeroY = zeroY;
            this.steps = steps;
        }

        String getKey() {
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                    sb.append(board[i][j]);
                }
            }
            return sb.toString();
        }

        boolean isTarget() {
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                    if (board[i][j] != TARGET[i][j]) {
                        return false;
                    }
                }
            }
            return true;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int[][] initial = new int[3][3];
        int zeroX = 0, zeroY = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                initial[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
                if (initial[i][j] == 0) {
                    zeroX = i;
                    zeroY = j;
                }
            }
        }

        Queue<State> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        Set<String> visited = new HashSet<>();

        State start = new State(initial, zeroX, zeroY, 0);
        queue.offer(start);
        visited.add(start.getKey());

        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            State current = queue.poll();

            if (current.isTarget()) {
                System.out.println(current.steps);
                return;
            }

            for (int d = 0; d < 4; d++) {
                int nx = current.zeroX + dx[d];
                int ny = current.zeroY + dy[d];

                if (nx >= 0 && nx < 3 && ny >= 0 && ny < 3) {
                    int[][] newBoard = new int[3][3];
                    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                        System.arraycopy(current.board[i], 0, newBoard[i], 0, 3);
                    }

                    newBoard[current.zeroX][current.zeroY] = newBoard[nx][ny];
                    newBoard[nx][ny] = 0;

                    State newState = new State(newBoard, nx, ny, current.steps + 1);
                    String key = newState.getKey();

                    if (!visited.contains(key)) {
                        visited.add(key);
                        queue.offer(newState);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
test/1/claude_p02245_1P.java: 1-100 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static final int[][] TARGET = {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}, {7, 8, 0}};
    static final int[] dx = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
    static final int[] dy = {0, 0, -1, 1};

    static class State {
        int[][] board;
        int zeroX, zeroY;
        int steps;

        State(int[][] board, int zeroX, int zeroY, int steps) {
            this.board = new int[3][3];
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                System.arraycopy(board[i], 0, this.board[i], 0, 3);
            }
            this.zeroX = zeroX;
            this.zeroY = zeroY;
            this.steps = steps;
        }

        String getKey() {
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                    sb.append(board[i][j]);
                }
            }
            return sb.toString();
        }

        boolean isTarget() {
            for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                    if (board[i][j] != TARGET[i][j]) {
                        return false;
                    }
                }
            }
            return true;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int[][] initial = new int[3][3];
        int zeroX = 0, zeroY = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
                initial[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
                if (initial[i][j] == 0) {
                    zeroX = i;
                    zeroY = j;
                }
            }
        }

        Queue<State> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        Set<String> visited = new HashSet<>();

        State start = new State(initial, zeroX, zeroY, 0);
        queue.offer(start);
        visited.add(start.getKey());

        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            State current = queue.poll();

            if (current.isTarget()) {
                System.out.println(current.steps);
                return;
            }

            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                int newX = current.zeroX + dx[i];
                int newY = current.zeroY + dy[i];

                if (newX >= 0 && newX < 3 && newY >= 0 && newY < 3) {
                    int[][] newBoard = new int[3][3];
                    for (int r = 0; r < 3; r++) {
                        System.arraycopy(current.board[r], 0, newBoard[r], 0, 3);
                    }

                    newBoard[current.zeroX][current.zeroY] = newBoard[newX][newY];
                    newBoard[newX][newY] = 0;

                    State newState = new State(newBoard, newX, newY, current.steps + 1);
                    String key = newState.getKey();

                    if (!visited.contains(key)) {
                        visited.add(key);
                        queue.offer(newState);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02260_0P.java: 1-42 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = scanner.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = scanner.nextInt();
        }

        int swapCount = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length - 1; i++) {
            int mini = i;
            for (int j = i; j < arr.length; j++) {
                if (arr[j] < arr[mini]) {
                    mini = j;
                }
            }
            if (i != mini) {
                int temp = arr[i];
                arr[i] = arr[mini];
                arr[mini] = temp;
                swapCount++;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (i > 0) System.out.print(" ");
            System.out.print(arr[i]);
        }
        System.out.println();

        System.out.println(swapCount);

        scanner.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02274_4P.java: 1-54 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    private static long inversions = 0;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        mergeSort(arr, 0, n - 1);
        System.out.println(inversions);
    }

    private static void mergeSort(int[] arr, int left, int right) {
        if (left < right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            mergeSort(arr, left, mid);
            mergeSort(arr, mid + 1, right);
            merge(arr, left, mid, right);
        }
    }

    private static void merge(int[] arr, int left, int mid, int right) {
        int[] temp = new int[right - left + 1];
        int i = left, j = mid + 1, k = 0;

        while (i <= mid && j <= right) {
            if (arr[i] <= arr[j]) {
                temp[k++] = arr[i++];
            } else {
                temp[k++] = arr[j++];
                inversions += (mid - i + 1);
            }
        }

        while (i <= mid) {
            temp[k++] = arr[i++];
        }

        while (j <= right) {
            temp[k++] = arr[j++];
        }

        for (i = left; i <= right; i++) {
            arr[i] = temp[i - left];
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    private static long inversions = 0;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        mergeSort(arr, 0, n - 1);
        System.out.println(inversions);
    }

    private static void mergeSort(int[] arr, int left, int right) {
        if (left < right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            mergeSort(arr, left, mid);
            mergeSort(arr, mid + 1, right);
            merge(arr, left, mid, right);
        }
    }

    private static void merge(int[] arr, int left, int mid, int right) {
        int[] temp = new int[right - left + 1];
        int i = left, j = mid + 1, k = 0;

        while (i <= mid && j <= right) {
            if (arr[i] <= arr[j]) {
                temp[k++] = arr[i++];
            } else {
                temp[k++] = arr[j++];
                inversions += (mid - i + 1);
            }
        }

        while (i <= mid) {
            temp[k++] = arr[i++];
        }

        while (j <= right) {
            temp[k++] = arr[j++];
        }

        for (i = left; i <= right; i++) {
            arr[i] = temp[i - left];
        }
    }

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class Node {
        int key, priority;
        Node left, right;

        Node(int key, int priority) {
            this.key = key;
            this.priority = priority;
            this.left = null;
            this.right = null;
        }
    }

    static class Treap {
        Node root;

        Treap() {
            root = null;
        }

        Node rightRotate(Node t) {
            Node s = t.left;
            t.left = s.right;
            s.right = t;
            return s;
        }

        Node leftRotate(Node t) {
            Node s = t.right;
            t.right = s.left;
            s.left = t;
            return s;
        }

        Node insert(Node t, int key, int priority) {
            if (t == null) {
                return new Node(key, priority);
            }
            if (key == t.key) {
                return t;
            }

            if (key < t.key) {
                t.left = insert(t.left, key, priority);
                if (t.priority < t.left.priority) {
                    t = rightRotate(t);
                }
            } else {
                t.right = insert(t.right, key, priority);
                if (t.priority < t.right.priority) {
                    t = leftRotate(t);
                }
            }
            return t;
        }

        Node delete(Node t, int key) {
            if (t == null) {
                return null;
            }
            if (key < t.key) {
                t.left = delete(t.left, key);
            } else if (key > t.key) {
                t.right = delete(t.right, key);
            } else {
                return _delete(t, key);
            }
            return t;
        }

        Node _delete(Node t, int key) {
            if (t.left == null && t.right == null) {
                return null;
            } else if (t.left == null) {
                t = leftRotate(t);
            } else if (t.right == null) {
                t = rightRotate(t);
            } else {
                if (t.left.priority > t.right.priority) {
                    t = rightRotate(t);
                } else {
                    t = leftRotate(t);
                }
            }
            return delete(t, key);
        }

        boolean find(Node t, int key) {
            if (t == null) {
                return false;
            }
            if (key == t.key) {
                return true;
            } else if (key < t.key) {
                return find(t.left, key);
            } else {
                return find(t.right, key);
            }
        }

        void inorder(Node t, List<Integer> result) {
            if (t != null) {
                inorder(t.left, result);
                result.add(t.key);
                inorder(t.right, result);
            }
        }

        void preorder(Node t, List<Integer> result) {
            if (t != null) {
                result.add(t.key);
                preorder(t.left, result);
                preorder(t.right, result);
            }
        }

        void insert(int key, int priority) {
            root = insert(root, key, priority);
        }

        void delete(int key) {
            root = delete(root, key);
        }

        boolean find(int key) {
            return find(root, key);
        }

        void print() {
            List<Integer> inorderResult = new ArrayList<>();
            List<Integer> preorderResult = new ArrayList<>();

            inorder(root, inorderResult);
            preorder(root, preorderResult);

            for (int key : inorderResult) {
                System.out.print(" " + key);
            }
            System.out.println();

            for (int key : preorderResult) {
                System.out.print(" " + key);
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int m = sc.nextInt();
        Treap treap = new Treap();

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            String operation = sc.next();

            if (operation.equals("insert")) {
                int k = sc.nextInt();
                int p = sc.nextInt();
                treap.insert(k, p);
            } else if (operation.equals("find")) {
                int k = sc.nextInt();
                if (treap.find(k)) {
                    System.out.println("yes");
                } else {
                    System.out.println("no");
                }
            } else if (operation.equals("delete")) {
                int k = sc.nextInt();
                treap.delete(k);
            } else if (operation.equals("print")) {
                treap.print();
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int H = scanner.nextInt();
        int[] heap = new int[H + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= H; i++) {
            heap[i] = scanner.nextInt();
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= H; i++) {
            System.out.print("node " + i + ": key = " + heap[i]);

            if (i > 1) {
                int parent = i / 2;
                System.out.print(", parent key = " + heap[parent]);
            }

            int left = 2 * i;
            if (left <= H) {
                System.out.print(", left key = " + heap[left]);
            }

            int right = 2 * i + 1;
            if (right <= H) {
                System.out.print(", right key = " + heap[right]);
            }

            System.out.println(", ");
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}

        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= H; i++) {
            System.out.print("node " + i + ": key = " + heap[i]);

            if (i > 1) {
                int parent = i / 2;
                System.out.print(", parent key = " + heap[parent]);
            }

            int left = 2 * i;
            if (left <= H) {
                System.out.print(", left key = " + heap[left]);
            }

            int right = 2 * i + 1;
            if (right <= H) {
                System.out.print(", right key = " + heap[right]);
            }

            System.out.println(", ");
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        double x1 = sc.nextDouble();
        double y1 = sc.nextDouble();
        double x2 = sc.nextDouble();
        double y2 = sc.nextDouble();

        int q = sc.nextInt();

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            double px = sc.nextDouble();
            double py = sc.nextDouble();

            double vx = x2 - x1;
            double vy = y2 - y1;

            double wx = px - x1;
            double wy = py - y1;

            double dot = wx * vx + wy * vy;

            double lenSq = vx * vx + vy * vy;

            double t = dot / lenSq;

            double projX = x1 + t * vx;
            double projY = y1 + t * vy;

            System.out.printf("%.10f %.10f%n", projX, projY);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02314_3P.java: 1-29 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();

        int[] coins = new int[m];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            coins[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];
        Arrays.fill(dp, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        dp[0] = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int coin : coins) {
                if (coin <= i && dp[i - coin] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[i - coin] + 1);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(dp[n]);
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02315_0P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int W = sc.nextInt();

        int[] values = new int[N];
        int[] weights = new int[N];

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            values[i] = sc.nextInt();
            weights[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int[][] dp = new int[N + 1][W + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int w = 0; w <= W; w++) {
                dp[i][w] = dp[i-1][w];

                if (w >= weights[i-1]) {
                    dp[i][w] = Math.max(dp[i][w], dp[i-1][w-weights[i-1]] + values[i-1]);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(dp[N][W]);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        List<Integer> lis = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int pos = Collections.binarySearch(lis, a[i]);
            if (pos < 0) {
                pos = -(pos + 1);
            }

            if (pos == lis.size()) {
                lis.add(a[i]);
            } else {
                lis.set(pos, a[i]);
            }
        }

        System.out.println(lis.size());
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02370_0P.java: 1-45 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int V = sc.nextInt();
        int E = sc.nextInt();

        List<List<Integer>> graph = new ArrayList<>();
        int[] inDegree = new int[V];

        for (int i = 0; i < V; i++) {
            graph.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < E; i++) {
            int s = sc.nextInt();
            int t = sc.nextInt();
            graph.get(s).add(t);
            inDegree[t]++;
        }

        Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < V; i++) {
            if (inDegree[i] == 0) {
                queue.offer(i);
            }
        }

        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            int current = queue.poll();
            System.out.println(current);

            for (int neighbor : graph.get(current)) {
                inDegree[neighbor]--;
                if (inDegree[neighbor] == 0) {
                    queue.offer(neighbor);
                }
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

Class 432:   2 fragments, nominal size 42 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p02378_1P.java: 1-52 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static List<Integer>[] graph;
    static int[] match;
    static boolean[] used;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int X = sc.nextInt();
        int Y = sc.nextInt();
        int E = sc.nextInt();

        graph = new List[X];
        for (int i = 0; i < X; i++) {
            graph[i] = new ArrayList<>();
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < E; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();
            int y = sc.nextInt();
            graph[x].add(y);
        }

        match = new int[Y];
        Arrays.fill(match, -1);

        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < X; i++) {
            used = new boolean[Y];
            if (dfs(i)) {
                result++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }

    static boolean dfs(int v) {
        for (int to : graph[v]) {
            if (used[to]) continue;
            used[to] = true;

            if (match[to] == -1 || dfs(match[to])) {
                match[to] = v;
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
test/1/claude_p02378_3P.java: 1-52 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static List<Integer>[] graph;
    static int[] match;
    static boolean[] used;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int X = sc.nextInt();
        int Y = sc.nextInt();
        int E = sc.nextInt();

        graph = new List[X];
        for (int i = 0; i < X; i++) {
            graph[i] = new ArrayList<>();
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < E; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();
            int y = sc.nextInt();
            graph[x].add(y);
        }

        match = new int[Y];
        Arrays.fill(match, -1);

        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < X; i++) {
            used = new boolean[Y];
            if (dfs(i)) {
                result++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }

    static boolean dfs(int v) {
        for (int to : graph[v]) {
            if (used[to]) continue;
            used[to] = true;

            if (match[to] == -1 || dfs(match[to])) {
                match[to] = v;
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02380_1P.java: 1-25 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Triangle {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        double a = sc.nextDouble();
        double b = sc.nextDouble();
        double C = sc.nextDouble();

        double C_rad = Math.toRadians(C);

        double S = 0.5 * a * b * Math.sin(C_rad);

        double c = Math.sqrt(a * a + b * b - 2 * a * b * Math.cos(C_rad));

        double L = a + b + c;

        double h = 2 * S / a;

        System.out.printf("%.8f\n", S);
        System.out.printf("%.8f\n", L);
        System.out.printf("%.8f\n", h);
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int x = scanner.nextInt();
            int y = scanner.nextInt();

            if (x == 0 && y == 0) {
                break;
            }

            if (x <= y) {
                System.out.println(x + " " + y);
            } else {
                System.out.println(y + " " + x);
            }
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02398_3P.java: 1-27 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int c = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i * i <= c; i++) {
            if (c % i == 0) {
                if (i >= a && i <= b) {
                    count++;
                }
                int complement = c / i;
                if (complement != i && complement >= a && complement <= b) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
        sc.close();
    }
}

Class 438:   2 fragments, nominal size 26 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p02406_1P.java: 1-30 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        call(n);
        sc.close();
    }

    static void call(int n) {
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (i % 3 == 0 || containsDigit3(i)) {
                System.out.print(" " + i);
            }
        }
        System.out.println();
    }

    static boolean containsDigit3(int x) {
        while (x > 0) {
            if (x % 10 == 3) {
                return true;
            }
            x /= 10;
        }
        return false;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        call(n);
        sc.close();
    }

    static void call(int n) {
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (i % 3 == 0 || containsDigit3(i)) {
                System.out.print(" " + i);
            }
        }
        System.out.println();
    }

    static boolean containsDigit3(int x) {
        while (x > 0) {
            if (x % 10 == 3) {
                return true;
            }
            x /= 10;
        }
        return false;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02406_4P.java: 1-31 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        call(n);
        sc.close();
    }

    static void call(int n) {
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            int x = i;

            if (x % 3 == 0) {
                System.out.print(" " + i);
                continue;
            }

            while (x > 0) {
                if (x % 10 == 3) {
                    System.out.print(" " + i);
                    break;
                }
                x /= 10;
            }
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

        sc.close();

train/1/claude_p02410_0P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] A = new int[n][m];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                A[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        int[] b = new int[m];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            b[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int sum = 0;
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                sum += A[i][j] * b[j];
            }
            System.out.println(sum);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] a = new int[n][m];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                a[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        int[] b = new int[m];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            b[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

train/1/claude_p02412_3P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            int x = scanner.nextInt();

            if (n == 0 && x == 0) {
                break;
            }

            int count = 0;

            for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
                for (int j = i + 1; j <= n; j++) {
                    for (int k = j + 1; k <= n; k++) {
                        if (i + j + k == x) {
                            count++;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            System.out.println(count);
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02417_1P.java: 1-24 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int[] count = new int[26];

        while (scanner.hasNextLine()) {
            String line = scanner.nextLine().toLowerCase();
            for (char c : line.toCharArray()) {
                if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
                    count[c - 'a']++;
                }
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
            System.out.println((char)('a' + i) + " : " + count[i]);
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02419_1P.java: 1-24 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        String word = scanner.nextLine().toLowerCase();
        int count = 0;

        String line;
        while (!(line = scanner.nextLine()).equals("END_OF_TEXT")) {
            String[] words = line.toLowerCase().split("\\s+");
            for (String w : words) {
                if (w.equals(word)) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
        scanner.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02420_0P.java: 1-28 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            String deck = sc.nextLine();
            if (deck.equals("-")) {
                break;
            }

            int m = sc.nextInt();

            for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
                int h = sc.nextInt();
                String bottom = deck.substring(0, h);
                String remaining = deck.substring(h);
                deck = remaining + bottom;
            }

            System.out.println(deck);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int q = sc.nextInt();

        int[] arr = new int[200000];
        int size = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();

            if (op == 0) {
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                arr[size++] = x;
            } else if (op == 1) {
                int p = sc.nextInt();
                System.out.println(arr[p]);
            } else {
                size--;
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p02437_0P.java: 1-36 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int q = sc.nextInt();

        PriorityQueue<Integer>[] queues = new PriorityQueue[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            queues[i] = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();
            if (op == 0) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                queues[t].offer(x);
            } else if (op == 1) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    System.out.println(queues[t].peek());
                }
            } else if (op == 2) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    queues[t].poll();
                }
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int q = sc.nextInt();

        PriorityQueue<Integer>[] queues = new PriorityQueue[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            queues[i] = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();
            if (op == 0) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                queues[t].add(x);
            } else if (op == 1) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    System.out.println(queues[t].peek());
                }
            } else if (op == 2) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    queues[t].poll();
                }
            }
        }

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int q = sc.nextInt();

        TreeSet<Integer>[] queues = new TreeSet[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            queues[i] = new TreeSet<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();

            if (op == 0) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                queues[t].add(x);
            } else if (op == 1) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    System.out.println(queues[t].first());
                }
            } else if (op == 2) {
                int t = sc.nextInt();
                if (!queues[t].isEmpty()) {
                    queues[t].pollFirst();
                }
            }

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int m = sc.nextInt();
        int[] b = new int[m];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            b[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        StringBuilder sbA = new StringBuilder();
        StringBuilder sbB = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            sbA.append(String.format("%04d", a[i]));
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            sbB.append(String.format("%04d", b[i]));
        }

        String strA = sbA.toString();
        String strB = sbB.toString();

        if (strB.compareTo(strA) > 0) {
            System.out.println(1);
        } else {
            System.out.println(0);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int q = sc.nextInt();

        Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();

            if (op == 0) {
                String key = sc.next();
                int value = sc.nextInt();
                map.put(key, value);
            } else if (op == 1) {
                String key = sc.next();
                System.out.println(map.get(key));
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int q = sc.nextInt();

        Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
            int op = sc.nextInt();

            if (op == 0) {
                String key = sc.next();
                int value = sc.nextInt();
                map.put(key, value);
            } else if (op == 1) {
                String key = sc.next();
                System.out.println(map.get(key));
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int S = sc.nextInt();

        final int MOD = 1000000007;
        long[] dp = new long[S + 1];
        dp[0] = 1;

        for (int i = 1; i <= S; i++) {
            for (int j = 3; j <= i; j++) {
                dp[i] = (dp[i] + dp[i - j]) % MOD;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(dp[S]);
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        long maxSum = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        long minSum = Long.MAX_VALUE;
        long maxDiff = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        long minDiff = Long.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            long x = sc.nextLong();
            long y = sc.nextLong();

            long sum = x + y;
            long diff = x - y;

            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, sum);
            minSum = Math.min(minSum, sum);
            maxDiff = Math.max(maxDiff, diff);
            minDiff = Math.min(minDiff, diff);
        }

        long result = Math.max(maxSum - minSum, maxDiff - minDiff);
        System.out.println(result);

        sc.close();
    }
}

        long maxSum = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        long minDiff = Long.MAX_VALUE;

            long x = sc.nextLong();
            long y = sc.nextLong();

            long sum = x + y;
            long diff = x - y;

            minSum = Math.min(minSum, sum);
            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, sum);
            minDiff = Math.min(minDiff, diff);
            maxDiff = Math.max(maxDiff, diff);
