Class 571:   3 fragments, nominal size 48 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03326_0P.java: 1-60 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class Cake {
        long x, y, z;

        Cake(long x, long y, long z) {
            this.x = x;
            this.y = y;
            this.z = z;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int M = sc.nextInt();

        Cake[] cakes = new Cake[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            long x = sc.nextLong();
            long y = sc.nextLong();
            long z = sc.nextLong();
            cakes[i] = new Cake(x, y, z);
        }

        long maxValue = 0;

        for (int mask = 0; mask < 8; mask++) {
            int sx = (mask & 1) == 0 ? 1 : -1;
            int sy = (mask & 2) == 0 ? 1 : -1;
            int sz = (mask & 4) == 0 ? 1 : -1;

            long[] scores = new long[N];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                scores[i] = sx * cakes[i].x + sy * cakes[i].y + sz * cakes[i].z;
            }

            Integer[] indices = new Integer[N];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                indices[i] = i;
            }
            Arrays.sort(indices, (a, b) -> Long.compare(scores[b], scores[a]));

            long totalX = 0, totalY = 0, totalZ = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < M; i++) {
                int idx = indices[i];
                totalX += cakes[idx].x;
                totalY += cakes[idx].y;
                totalZ += cakes[idx].z;
            }

            long value = Math.abs(totalX) + Math.abs(totalY) + Math.abs(totalZ);
            maxValue = Math.max(maxValue, value);
        }

        System.out.println(maxValue);
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class Cake {
        long x, y, z;
        Cake(long x, long y, long z) {
            this.x = x;
            this.y = y;
            this.z = z;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int M = sc.nextInt();

        Cake[] cakes = new Cake[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            long x = sc.nextLong();
            long y = sc.nextLong();
            long z = sc.nextLong();
            cakes[i] = new Cake(x, y, z);
        }

        long maxValue = 0;

        for (int mask = 0; mask < 8; mask++) {
            int sx = (mask & 1) == 0 ? 1 : -1;
            int sy = (mask & 2) == 0 ? 1 : -1;
            int sz = (mask & 4) == 0 ? 1 : -1;

            long[] values = new long[N];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                values[i] = sx * cakes[i].x + sy * cakes[i].y + sz * cakes[i].z;
            }

            Integer[] indices = new Integer[N];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                indices[i] = i;
            }
            Arrays.sort(indices, (a, b) -> Long.compare(values[b], values[a]));

            long totalX = 0, totalY = 0, totalZ = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < M; i++) {
                int idx = indices[i];
                totalX += cakes[idx].x;
                totalY += cakes[idx].y;
                totalZ += cakes[idx].z;
            }

            long currentValue = Math.abs(totalX) + Math.abs(totalY) + Math.abs(totalZ);
            maxValue = Math.max(maxValue, currentValue);
        }

        System.out.println(maxValue);
    }
}

Class 572:   3 fragments, nominal size 49 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03330_0P.java: 1-62 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int C = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] D = new int[C+1][C+1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= C; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= C; j++) {
                D[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        int[][] grid = new int[N+1][N+1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= N; j++) {
                grid[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        List<List<Integer>> groups = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int k = 0; k < 3; k++) {
            groups.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= N; j++) {
                int group = (i + j) % 3;
                groups.get(group).add(grid[i][j]);
            }
        }

        long minCost = Long.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int c1 = 1; c1 <= C; c1++) {
            for (int c2 = 1; c2 <= C; c2++) {
                if (c2 == c1) continue;
                for (int c3 = 1; c3 <= C; c3++) {
                    if (c3 == c1 || c3 == c2) continue;

                    int[] colors = {c1, c2, c3};
                    long cost = 0;

                    for (int g = 0; g < 3; g++) {
                        int targetColor = colors[g];
                        for (int originalColor : groups.get(g)) {
                            cost += D[originalColor][targetColor];
                        }
                    }

                    minCost = Math.min(minCost, cost);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(minCost);
    }
}

        for (int c1 = 1; c1 <= C; c1++) {
            for (int c2 = 1; c2 <= C; c2++) {
                if (c2 == c1) continue;
                for (int c3 = 1; c3 <= C; c3++) {
                    if (c3 == c1 || c3 == c2) continue;

                    int[] colors = {c1, c2, c3};
                    long cost = 0;

                    for (int group = 0; group < 3; group++) {
                        int targetColor = colors[group];
                        for (int originalColor : groups.get(group)) {
                            cost += D[originalColor][targetColor];
                        }
                    }

                    minCost = Math.min(minCost, cost);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(minCost);
    }
}
train/1/claude_p03330_1P.java: 1-62 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int C = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] D = new int[C + 1][C + 1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= C; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= C; j++) {
                D[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        int[][] grid = new int[N + 1][N + 1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= N; j++) {
                grid[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        List<List<Integer>> groups = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int k = 0; k < 3; k++) {
            groups.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= N; j++) {
                int group = (i + j) % 3;
                groups.get(group).add(grid[i][j]);
            }
        }

        long minCost = Long.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int c1 = 1; c1 <= C; c1++) {
            for (int c2 = 1; c2 <= C; c2++) {
                if (c2 == c1) continue;
                for (int c3 = 1; c3 <= C; c3++) {
                    if (c3 == c1 || c3 == c2) continue;

                    int[] colors = {c1, c2, c3};
                    long totalCost = 0;

                    for (int g = 0; g < 3; g++) {
                        int targetColor = colors[g];
                        for (int originalColor : groups.get(g)) {
                            totalCost += D[originalColor][targetColor];
                        }
                    }

                    minCost = Math.min(minCost, totalCost);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(minCost);
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03331_1P.java: 1-28 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int minSum = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int A = 1; A < N; A++) {
            int B = N - A;
            int sum = digitSum(A) + digitSum(B);
            minSum = Math.min(minSum, sum);
        }

        System.out.println(minSum);
    }

    private static int digitSum(int n) {
        int sum = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            sum += n % 10;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return sum;
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        String s = sc.next();

        int[] leftW = new int[n];
        leftW[0] = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            leftW[i] = leftW[i-1] + (s.charAt(i-1) == 'W' ? 1 : 0);
        }

        int[] rightE = new int[n];
        rightE[n-1] = 0;
        for (int i = n-2; i >= 0; i--) {
            rightE[i] = rightE[i+1] + (s.charAt(i+1) == 'E' ? 1 : 0);
        }

        int minChanges = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int changes = leftW[i] + rightE[i];
            minChanges = Math.min(minChanges, changes);
        }

        System.out.println(minChanges);
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        long A = sc.nextLong();
        long B = sc.nextLong();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        Set<Long> result = new TreeSet<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < K && A + i <= B; i++) {
            result.add(A + i);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < K && B - i >= A; i++) {
            result.add(B - i);
        }

        for (long num : result) {
            System.out.println(num);
        }
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03416_4P.java: 1-31 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int A = sc.nextInt();
        int B = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = A; i <= B; i++) {
            if (isPalindrome(i)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }

    private static boolean isPalindrome(int num) {
        String str = String.valueOf(num);
        int len = str.length();

        for (int i = 0; i < len / 2; i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) != str.charAt(len - 1 - i)) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int A = sc.nextInt();
        int B = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = A; i <= B; i++) {
            if (isPalindrome(i)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }

    private static boolean isPalindrome(int num) {
        String str = String.valueOf(num);
        int len = str.length();

        for (int i = 0; i < len / 2; i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) != str.charAt(len - 1 - i)) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int H = sc.nextInt();
        int W = sc.nextInt();
        int D = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] pos = new int[H * W + 1][2];

        for (int i = 0; i < H; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < W; j++) {
                int num = sc.nextInt();
                pos[num][0] = i;
                pos[num][1] = j;
            }
        }

        long[] cumCost = new long[H * W + 1];

        for (int start = 1; start <= D; start++) {
            for (int curr = start; curr + D <= H * W; curr += D) {
                int next = curr + D;
                int cost = Math.abs(pos[next][0] - pos[curr][0]) +
                          Math.abs(pos[next][1] - pos[curr][1]);
                cumCost[next] = cumCost[curr] + cost;
            }
        }

        int Q = sc.nextInt();
        for (int i = 0; i < Q; i++) {
            int L = sc.nextInt();
            int R = sc.nextInt();
            System.out.println(cumCost[R] - cumCost[L]);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

                int val = sc.nextInt();
                pos[val][0] = i;
                pos[val][1] = j;

            int L = sc.nextInt();
            int R = sc.nextInt();

        int A = sc.nextInt();
        int B = sc.nextInt();
        int C = sc.nextInt();
        int X = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= A; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= B; j++) {
                for (int k = 0; k <= C; k++) {

train/1/claude_p03449_0P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int[][] A = new int[2][N];
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
                A[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
        }

        int[][] dp = new int[2][N];

        dp[0][0] = A[0][0];

        for (int j = 1; j < N; j++) {
            dp[0][j] = dp[0][j-1] + A[0][j];
        }

        dp[1][0] = dp[0][0] + A[1][0];
        for (int j = 1; j < N; j++) {
            dp[1][j] = Math.max(dp[0][j], dp[1][j-1]) + A[1][j];
        }

        System.out.println(dp[1][N-1]);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();

        String concatenated = String.valueOf(a) + String.valueOf(b);
        long number = Long.parseLong(concatenated);

        long sqrt = (long) Math.sqrt(number);

        if (sqrt * sqrt == number) {
            System.out.println("Yes");
        } else {
            System.out.println("No");
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03487_4P.java: 1-31 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        Map<Integer, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();
            freq.put(a, freq.getOrDefault(a, 0) + 1);
        }

        int toRemove = 0;

        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : freq.entrySet()) {
            int value = entry.getKey();
            int count = entry.getValue();

            if (count > value) {
                toRemove += count - value;
            } else if (count < value) {
                toRemove += count;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(toRemove);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();

        String target = "AKIHABARA";

        StringBuilder sNonA = new StringBuilder();
        StringBuilder targetNonA = new StringBuilder();

        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c != 'A') {
                sNonA.append(c);
            }
        }

        for (char c : target.toCharArray()) {
            if (c != 'A') {
                targetNonA.append(c);
            }
        }

        if (sNonA.toString().equals(targetNonA.toString())) {
            System.out.println("YES");
        } else {
            System.out.println("NO");
        }
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03557_1P.java: 1-66 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[] a = new int[n];
        int[] b = new int[n];
        int[] c = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            b[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            c[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        Arrays.sort(a);
        Arrays.sort(c);

        long result = 0;

        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            int middle = b[j];

            int upperCount = countSmaller(a, middle);

            int lowerCount = countLarger(c, middle);

            result += (long) upperCount * lowerCount;
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }

    private static int countSmaller(int[] arr, int target) {
        int left = 0, right = arr.length;
        while (left < right) {
            int mid = (left + right) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] < target) {
                left = mid + 1;
            } else {
                right = mid;
            }
        }
        return left;
    }

    private static int countLarger(int[] arr, int target) {
        int left = 0, right = arr.length;
        while (left < right) {
            int mid = (left + right) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] <= target) {
                left = mid + 1;
            } else {
                right = mid;
            }
        }
        return arr.length - left;
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[] a = new int[n];
        int[] b = new int[n];
        int[] c = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            b[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            c[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        Arrays.sort(a);
        Arrays.sort(c);

        long result = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int middle = b[i];

            int upperCount = countLess(a, middle);

            int lowerCount = countGreater(c, middle);

            result += (long) upperCount * lowerCount;
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }

    private static int countLess(int[] arr, int target) {
        int left = 0, right = arr.length;
        while (left < right) {
            int mid = (left + right) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] < target) {
                left = mid + 1;
            } else {
                right = mid;
            }
        }
        return left;
    }

    private static int countGreater(int[] arr, int target) {
        int left = 0, right = arr.length;
        while (left < right) {
            int mid = (left + right) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] <= target) {
                left = mid + 1;
            } else {
                right = mid;
            }
        }
        return arr.length - left;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03578_2P.java: 1-37 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        Map<Integer, Integer> candidates = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int d = sc.nextInt();
            candidates.put(d, candidates.getOrDefault(d, 0) + 1);
        }

        int M = sc.nextInt();
        Map<Integer, Integer> required = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < M; i++) {
            int t = sc.nextInt();
            required.put(t, required.getOrDefault(t, 0) + 1);
        }

        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : required.entrySet()) {
            int difficulty = entry.getKey();
            int neededCount = entry.getValue();
            int availableCount = candidates.getOrDefault(difficulty, 0);

            if (availableCount < neededCount) {
                System.out.println("NO");
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("YES");
    }
}

        System.out.println("YES");

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        int totalDistance = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();

            int costA = 2 * x;

            int costB = 2 * (K - x);

            totalDistance += Math.min(costA, costB);
        }

        System.out.println(totalDistance);
        sc.close();
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        int totalDistance = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();

            int costA = 2 * x;

            int costB = 2 * (K - x);

            totalDistance += Math.min(costA, costB);
        }

        System.out.println(totalDistance);
        sc.close();
    }

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();
        int totalDistance = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();
            int distA = 2 * x;
            int distB = 2 * (K - x);
            totalDistance += Math.min(distA, distB);
        }
        System.out.println(totalDistance);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long[][] a = new long[n][n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                a[i][j] = sc.nextLong();
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
                    if (a[i][j] > a[i][k] + a[k][j]) {
                        System.out.println(-1);
                        return;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        boolean[][] necessary = new boolean[n][n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                necessary[i][j] = true;
                for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
                    if (k != i && k != j && a[i][j] == a[i][k] + a[k][j]) {
                        necessary[i][j] = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        long totalLength = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (necessary[i][j]) {
                    totalLength += a[i][j];
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(totalLength);
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long[][] a = new long[n][n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                a[i][j] = sc.nextLong();
            }
        }

        long[][] dist = new long[n][n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                dist[i][j] = a[i][j];
            }
        }

        for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                    if (dist[i][k] + dist[k][j] < dist[i][j]) {
                        System.out.println(-1);
                        return;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        boolean[][] necessary = new boolean[n][n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                necessary[i][j] = true;
                for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
                    if (k != i && k != j && a[i][k] + a[k][j] == a[i][j]) {
                        necessary[i][j] = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        long totalLength = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (necessary[i][j]) {
                    totalLength += a[i][j];
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(totalLength);
    }
}

public class Main {

                        System.out.println(-1);

Class 604:   2 fragments, nominal size 26 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03611_1P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        Set<Integer> candidates = new HashSet<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
            candidates.add(a[i] - 1);
            candidates.add(a[i]);
            candidates.add(a[i] + 1);
        }

        int maxCount = 0;

        for (int x : candidates) {
            int count = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                if (Math.abs(a[i] - x) <= 1) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            maxCount = Math.max(maxCount, count);
        }

        System.out.println(maxCount);
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03612_4P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] p = new int[n + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            p[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int swaps = 0;
        int i = 1;

        while (i <= n) {
            if (p[i] == i) {
                int segmentLength = 0;
                while (i <= n && p[i] == i) {
                    segmentLength++;
                    i++;
                }
                swaps += (segmentLength + 1) / 2;
            } else {
                i++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(swaps);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03618_1P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String A = sc.next();
        int n = A.length();

        Set<String> uniqueStrings = new HashSet<>();

        uniqueStrings.add(A);

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
                StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

                sb.append(A.substring(0, i));

                for (int k = j; k >= i; k--) {
                    sb.append(A.charAt(k));
                }

                sb.append(A.substring(j + 1));

                uniqueStrings.add(sb.toString());
            }
        }

        System.out.println(uniqueStrings.size());
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int x = sc.nextInt();
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();

        int distanceA = Math.abs(x - a);
        int distanceB = Math.abs(x - b);

        if (distanceA < distanceB) {

train/1/claude_p03625_1P.java: 1-40 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        Map<Integer, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();
        for (int length : a) {
            freq.put(length, freq.getOrDefault(length, 0) + 1);
        }

        List<Integer> pairs = new ArrayList<>();
        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : freq.entrySet()) {
            int length = entry.getKey();
            int count = entry.getValue();

            for (int i = 0; i < count / 2; i++) {
                pairs.add(length);
            }
        }

        pairs.sort(Collections.reverseOrder());

        if (pairs.size() < 2) {
            System.out.println(0);
        } else {
            long area = (long) pairs.get(0) * pairs.get(1);
            System.out.println(area);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}
test/1/claude_p03625_3P.java: 1-40 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        Map<Integer, Integer> count = new HashMap<>();
        for (int stick : a) {
            count.put(stick, count.getOrDefault(stick, 0) + 1);
        }

        List<Integer> pairs = new ArrayList<>();
        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : count.entrySet()) {
            int length = entry.getKey();
            int freq = entry.getValue();

            for (int i = 0; i < freq / 2; i++) {
                pairs.add(length);
            }
        }

        pairs.sort(Collections.reverseOrder());

        if (pairs.size() < 2) {
            System.out.println(0);
        } else {
            long area = (long) pairs.get(0) * pairs.get(1);
            System.out.println(area);
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03661_0P.java: 1-29 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long[] a = new long[n];
        long totalSum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextLong();
            totalSum += a[i];
        }

        long minDiff = Long.MAX_VALUE;
        long snukeSum = 0;

        for (int k = 1; k < n; k++) {
            snukeSum += a[k-1];
            long raccoonSum = totalSum - snukeSum;
            long diff = Math.abs(snukeSum - raccoonSum);
            minDiff = Math.min(minDiff, diff);
        }

        System.out.println(minDiff);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03673_1P.java: 1-41 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        ArrayDeque<Integer> deque = new ArrayDeque<>();
        boolean reversed = false;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();

            if (!reversed) {
                deque.addLast(a);
            } else {
                deque.addFirst(a);
            }

            reversed = !reversed;
        }

        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        if (!reversed) {
            while (!deque.isEmpty()) {
                result.add(deque.removeFirst());
            }
        } else {
            while (!deque.isEmpty()) {
                result.add(deque.removeLast());
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < result.size(); i++) {
            if (i > 0) System.out.print(" ");
            System.out.print(result.get(i));
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03677_0P.java: 1-35 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int minCost = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int x = 1; x <= m; x++) {
            int totalCost = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
                int current = a[i];
                int target = a[i + 1];

                int forwardOnly = (target - current + m) % m;

                int favoriteFirst = 1 + (target - x + m) % m;

                totalCost += Math.min(forwardOnly, favoriteFirst);
            }

            minCost = Math.min(minCost, totalCost);
        }

        System.out.println(minCost);
    }
}

Class 617:   9 fragments, nominal size 78 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03682_0P.java: 1-95 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class Edge implements Comparable<Edge> {
        int u, v, cost;

        Edge(int u, int v, int cost) {
            this.u = u;
            this.v = v;
            this.cost = cost;
        }

        public int compareTo(Edge other) {
            return Integer.compare(this.cost, other.cost);
        }
    }

    static class UnionFind {
        int[] parent, rank;

        UnionFind(int n) {
            parent = new int[n];
            rank = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                parent[i] = i;
            }
        }

        int find(int x) {
            if (parent[x] != x) {
                parent[x] = find(parent[x]);
            }
            return parent[x];
        }

        boolean union(int x, int y) {
            int px = find(x), py = find(y);
            if (px == py) return false;

            if (rank[px] < rank[py]) {
                parent[px] = py;
            } else if (rank[px] > rank[py]) {
                parent[py] = px;
            } else {
                parent[py] = px;
                rank[px]++;
            }
            return true;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int M = sc.nextInt();

        int[] count = new int[N + 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < M; i++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();
            int b = sc.nextInt();
            count[a]++;
            count[b]++;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            if (count[i] % 2 != 0) {
                System.out.println("NO");
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("YES");
    }
}

Class 620:   2 fragments, nominal size 36 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03739_3P.java: 1-44 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long[] a = new long[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long cost1 = solve(a, true);
        long cost2 = solve(a, false);

        System.out.println(Math.min(cost1, cost2));
    }

    static long solve(long[] a, boolean startPositive) {
        int n = a.length;
        long cost = 0;
        long prefixSum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            prefixSum += a[i];

            boolean shouldBePositive = (i % 2 == 0) ? startPositive : !startPositive;

            if (shouldBePositive) {
                if (prefixSum < 1) {
                    cost += 1 - prefixSum;
                    prefixSum = 1;
                }
            } else {
                if (prefixSum > -1) {
                    cost += prefixSum - (-1);
                    prefixSum = -1;
                }
            }
        }

        return cost;
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long[] a = new long[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long cost1 = solve(a, true);
        long cost2 = solve(a, false);

        System.out.println(Math.min(cost1, cost2));
    }

    static long solve(long[] a, boolean startPositive) {
        int n = a.length;
        long operations = 0;
        long prefixSum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            prefixSum += a[i];

            boolean shouldBePositive = (i % 2 == 0) ? startPositive : !startPositive;

            if (shouldBePositive) {
                if (prefixSum < 1) {
                    operations += 1 - prefixSum;
                    prefixSum = 1;
                }
            } else {
                if (prefixSum > -1) {
                    operations += prefixSum - (-1);
                    prefixSum = -1;
                }
            }
        }

        return operations;
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03761_4P.java: 1-38 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        String[] strings = new String[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            strings[i] = sc.next();
        }

        int[][] freq = new int[n][26];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (char c : strings[i].toCharArray()) {
                freq[i][c - 'a']++;
            }
        }

        int[] minFreq = new int[26];
        for (int j = 0; j < 26; j++) {
            minFreq[j] = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                minFreq[j] = Math.min(minFreq[j], freq[i][j]);
            }
        }

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        for (int j = 0; j < 26; j++) {
            for (int k = 0; k < minFreq[j]; k++) {
                result.append((char)('a' + j));
            }
        }

        System.out.println(result.toString());
    }
}

Class 625:   2 fragments, nominal size 38 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03823_1P.java: 1-48 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static final int MOD = 1000000007;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long a = sc.nextLong();
        long b = sc.nextLong();

        long[] s = new long[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            s[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long[][][] dp = new long[n + 1][n + 1][n + 1];
        dp[0][n][n] = 1;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
                for (int k = 0; k <= n; k++) {
                    if (dp[i][j][k] == 0) continue;

                    boolean canAddToX = (j == n) || (s[i] - s[j] >= a);
                    if (canAddToX) {
                        dp[i + 1][i][k] = (dp[i + 1][i][k] + dp[i][j][k]) % MOD;
                    }

                    boolean canAddToY = (k == n) || (s[i] - s[k] >= b);
                    if (canAddToY) {
                        dp[i + 1][j][i] = (dp[i + 1][j][i] + dp[i][j][k]) % MOD;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        long result = 0;
        for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
            for (int k = 0; k <= n; k++) {
                result = (result + dp[n][j][k]) % MOD;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }
}
test/1/claude_p03823_3P.java: 1-48 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static final int MOD = 1000000007;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        long a = sc.nextLong();
        long b = sc.nextLong();

        long[] s = new long[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            s[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long[][][] dp = new long[n + 1][n + 1][n + 1];
        dp[0][n][n] = 1;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
                for (int k = 0; k <= n; k++) {
                    if (dp[i][j][k] == 0) continue;

                    boolean canPutInX = (j == n) || (s[i] - s[j] >= a);
                    if (canPutInX) {
                        dp[i + 1][i][k] = (dp[i + 1][i][k] + dp[i][j][k]) % MOD;
                    }

                    boolean canPutInY = (k == n) || (s[i] - s[k] >= b);
                    if (canPutInY) {
                        dp[i + 1][j][i] = (dp[i + 1][j][i] + dp[i][j][k]) % MOD;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        long result = 0;
        for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
            for (int k = 0; k <= n; k++) {
                result = (result + dp[n][j][k]) % MOD;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(result);
    }

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        String s = sc.next();

        int x = 0;
        int maxX = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == 'I') {
                x++;
            } else {
                x--;
            }
            maxX = Math.max(maxX, x);
        }

        System.out.println(maxX);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int N = sc.nextInt();
        long A = sc.nextLong();
        long B = sc.nextLong();

        long[] X = new long[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            X[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long totalFatigue = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < N - 1; i++) {
            long distance = X[i + 1] - X[i];
            long walkCost = A * distance;
            long teleportCost = B;

            totalFatigue += Math.min(walkCost, teleportCost);
        }

        System.out.println(totalFatigue);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        long A = sc.nextLong();
        long B = sc.nextLong();
        long[] X = new long[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            X[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        long totalFatigue = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < N - 1; i++) {
            long distance = X[i + 1] - X[i];
            long walkCost = distance * A;
            long teleportCost = B;

            totalFatigue += Math.min(walkCost, teleportCost);
        }

        System.out.println(totalFatigue);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int K = sc.nextInt();
        int S = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 0;

        for (int X = 0; X <= K; X++) {
            for (int Y = 0; Y <= K; Y++) {
                int Z = S - X - Y;
                if (Z >= 0 && Z <= K) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int sx = sc.nextInt();
        int sy = sc.nextInt();
        int tx = sc.nextInt();
        int ty = sc.nextInt();

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < tx - sx; i++) {
            result.append('R');
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < ty - sy; i++) {
            result.append('U');
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < ty - sy; i++) {
            result.append('D');
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < tx - sx; i++) {
            result.append('L');
        }

        result.append('L');
        for (int i = 0; i < ty - sy + 1; i++) {
            result.append('U');
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < tx - sx + 1; i++) {
            result.append('R');
        }
        result.append('D');

        result.append('R');
        for (int i = 0; i < ty - sy + 1; i++) {
            result.append('D');
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < tx - sx + 1; i++) {
            result.append('L');
        }
        result.append('U');

        System.out.println(result.toString());
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03854_0P.java: 1-30 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();

        String[] words = {"dream", "dreamer", "erase", "eraser"};

        while (s.length() > 0) {
            boolean found = false;

            for (String word : words) {
                if (s.endsWith(word)) {
                    s = s.substring(0, s.length() - word.length());
                    found = true;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (!found) {
                System.out.println("NO");
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("YES");
    }
}

Class 631:   3 fragments, nominal size 66 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/claude_p03855_2P.java: 1-78 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class UnionFind {
        int[] parent, size;

        UnionFind(int n) {
            parent = new int[n];
            size = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                parent[i] = i;
                size[i] = 1;
            }
        }

        int find(int x) {
            if (parent[x] != x) {
                parent[x] = find(parent[x]);
            }
            return parent[x];
        }

        void union(int x, int y) {
            x = find(x);
            y = find(y);
            if (x != y) {
                if (size[x] < size[y]) {
                    int temp = x;
                    x = y;
                    y = temp;
                }
                parent[y] = x;
                size[x] += size[y];
            }
        }

        boolean connected(int x, int y) {
            return find(x) == find(y);
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();
        int L = sc.nextInt();

        UnionFind roadUF = new UnionFind(N);
        UnionFind railUF = new UnionFind(N);

        for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
            int p = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            int q = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            roadUF.union(p, q);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < L; i++) {
            int r = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            int s = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            railUF.union(r, s);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int count = 0;
            for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
                if (roadUF.connected(i, j) && railUF.connected(i, j)) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            System.out.print(count);
            if (i < N - 1) System.out.print(" ");
        }
        System.out.println();

        sc.close();
    }
}

                size[i] = 1;
            }

                parent[x] = find(parent[x]);
            }
            return parent[x];
        }

        void union(int x, int y) {
            x = find(x);
            y = find(y);
            if (x != y) {
                if (size[x] < size[y]) {

                }
                parent[y] = x;
                size[x] += size[y];
            }
        }

        boolean connected(int x, int y) {
            return find(x) == find(y);
        }
    }

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static class UnionFind {
        int[] parent, size;

        UnionFind(int n) {
            parent = new int[n];
            size = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                parent[i] = i;
                size[i] = 1;
            }
        }

        int find(int x) {
            if (parent[x] != x) {
                parent[x] = find(parent[x]);
            }
            return parent[x];
        }

        void union(int x, int y) {
            x = find(x);
            y = find(y);
            if (x != y) {
                if (size[x] < size[y]) {
                    int temp = x;
                    x = y;
                    y = temp;
                }
                parent[y] = x;
                size[x] += size[y];
            }
        }

        boolean connected(int x, int y) {
            return find(x) == find(y);
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();
        int L = sc.nextInt();

        UnionFind roads = new UnionFind(N);
        UnionFind railways = new UnionFind(N);

        for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
            int p = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            int q = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            roads.union(p, q);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < L; i++) {
            int r = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            int s = sc.nextInt() - 1;
            railways.union(r, s);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int count = 0;
            for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
                if (roads.connected(i, j) && railways.connected(i, j)) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            System.out.print(count);
            if (i < N - 1) System.out.print(" ");
        }
        System.out.println();

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03944_0P.java: 1-38 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int W = sc.nextInt();
        int H = sc.nextInt();
        int N = sc.nextInt();

        int minX = 0, maxX = W;
        int minY = 0, maxY = H;

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            int x = sc.nextInt();
            int y = sc.nextInt();
            int a = sc.nextInt();

            if (a == 1) {
                minX = Math.max(minX, x);
            } else if (a == 2) {
                maxX = Math.min(maxX, x);
            } else if (a == 3) {
                minY = Math.max(minY, y);
            } else if (a == 4) {
                maxY = Math.min(maxY, y);
            }
        }

        int width = Math.max(0, maxX - minX);
        int height = Math.max(0, maxY - minY);
        int area = width * height;

        System.out.println(area);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int c = sc.nextInt();

        int count = 1;

        if (b != a) count++;
        if (c != a && c != b) count++;

        System.out.println(count);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03964_1P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        long takahashi = 0;
        long aoki = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            long t = sc.nextLong();
            long a = sc.nextLong();

            if (i == 0) {
                takahashi = t;
                aoki = a;
            } else {
                long k1 = (takahashi + t - 1) / t;
                long k2 = (aoki + a - 1) / a;
                long k = Math.max(k1, k2);

                takahashi = k * t;
                aoki = k * a;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(takahashi + aoki);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03971_0P.java: 1-40 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int A = sc.nextInt();
        int B = sc.nextInt();
        String S = sc.next();

        int totalPassed = 0;
        int overseasPassed = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            char participant = S.charAt(i);

            if (participant == 'a') {
                if (totalPassed < A + B) {
                    System.out.println("Yes");
                    totalPassed++;
                } else {
                    System.out.println("No");
                }
            } else if (participant == 'b') {
                if (totalPassed < A + B && overseasPassed < B) {
                    System.out.println("Yes");
                    totalPassed++;
                    overseasPassed++;
                } else {
                    System.out.println("No");
                }
            } else {
                System.out.println("No");
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p03993_0P.java: 1-27 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int friendlyPairs = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j <= n; j++) {
                if (a[i] == j && a[j] == i) {
                    friendlyPairs++;
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(friendlyPairs);
        sc.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();
        int n = s.length();

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i + 1)) {
                System.out.println((i + 1) + " " + (i + 2));
                return;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i + 2)) {
                System.out.println((i + 1) + " " + (i + 3));
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("-1 -1");
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class UnbalancedString {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();
        int n = s.length();

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i + 1)) {
                System.out.println((i + 1) + " " + (i + 2));
                return;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i + 2)) {
                System.out.println((i + 1) + " " + (i + 3));
                return;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("-1 -1");
    }

train/1/claude_p04031_1P.java: 1-31 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int minCost = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int target = -100; target <= 100; target++) {
            int cost = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                if (a[i] != target) {
                    cost += (a[i] - target) * (a[i] - target);
                }
            }

            minCost = Math.min(minCost, cost);
        }

        System.out.println(minCost);
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/claude_p04039_3P.java: 1-35 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int K = sc.nextInt();

        Set<Integer> disliked = new HashSet<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < K; i++) {
            disliked.add(sc.nextInt());
        }

        int amount = N;
        while (true) {
            if (isValid(amount, disliked)) {
                System.out.println(amount);
                break;
            }
            amount++;
        }
    }

    private static boolean isValid(int num, Set<Integer> disliked) {
        String str = String.valueOf(num);
        for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
            int digit = c - '0';
            if (disliked.contains(digit)) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

public class NationalBudget {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = scanner.nextInt();
        scanner.nextLine();

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            String num1 = scanner.nextLine().trim();
            String num2 = scanner.nextLine().trim();

            BigInteger a = new BigInteger(num1);
            BigInteger b = new BigInteger(num2);
            BigInteger sum = a.add(b);

            String sumStr = sum.toString();
            if (sumStr.length() > 80) {
                System.out.println("overflow");
            } else {
                System.out.println(sumStr);
            }
        }
    }
}

train/1/deepseek_p00025_1P.java: 1-33 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class HitAndBlow {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (scanner.hasNext()) {
            int[] a = new int[4];
            int[] b = new int[4];
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                a[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            }
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                b[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            }

            int hit = 0, blow = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                if (a[i] == b[i]) {
                    hit++;
                }
            }
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
                    if (i != j && a[i] == b[j]) {
                        blow++;
                    }
                }
            }
            System.out.println(hit + " " + blow);
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (sc.hasNext()) {
            double a = sc.nextDouble();
            double sum = 0;
            double current = a;
            sum += current;

            for (int i = 2; i <= 10; i++) {
                if (i % 2 == 0) {
                    current *= 2;
                } else {
                    current /= 3;
                }
                sum += current;
            }
            System.out.printf("%.8f\n", sum);
        }
        sc.close();
    }

train/1/deepseek_p00063_1P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int count = 0;

        while (scanner.hasNextLine()) {
            String line = scanner.nextLine().trim();
            if (isPalindrome(line)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }

    private static boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = s.length() - 1;

        while (left < right) {
            if (s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) {
                return false;
            }
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return true;
    }
}

train/1/deepseek_p00100_0P.java: 1-44 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            Map<Integer, Long> employeeSales = new HashMap<>();
            List<Integer> order = new ArrayList<>();

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int id = scanner.nextInt();
                int p = scanner.nextInt();
                int q = scanner.nextInt();

                long sales = (long) p * q;
                employeeSales.put(id, employeeSales.getOrDefault(id, 0L) + sales);

                if (!order.contains(id)) {
                    order.add(id);
                }
            }

            List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int id : order) {
                if (employeeSales.get(id) >= 1000000) {
                    result.add(id);
                }
            }

            if (result.isEmpty()) {
                System.out.println("NA");
            } else {
                for (int id : result) {
                    System.out.println(id);
                }
            }
        }
        scanner.close();
    }
}

import java.util.*;

public class SaleResult {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;
            Map<Integer, Long> map = new HashMap<>();
            List<Integer> order = new ArrayList<>();

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int id = sc.nextInt();
                int p = sc.nextInt();
                int q = sc.nextInt();
                long total = (long) p * q;
                map.put(id, map.getOrDefault(id, 0L) + total);
                if (!order.contains(id)) {
                    order.add(id);
                }
            }

            List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int id : order) {
                if (map.get(id) >= 1000000) {
                    result.add(id);
                }
            }

            if (result.isEmpty()) {
                System.out.println("NA");
            } else {
                for (int id : result) {
                    System.out.println(id);
                }
            }
        }
        sc.close();
    }
}

train/1/deepseek_p00112_1P.java: 1-26 
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class MilkShop {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;
            int[] times = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                times[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            }
            Arrays.sort(times);
            int totalWaitTime = 0;
            int cumulativeTime = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
                cumulativeTime += times[i];
                totalWaitTime += cumulativeTime;
            }
            System.out.println(totalWaitTime);
        }
        scanner.close();
    }
}

        int n = scanner.nextInt();
        scanner.nextLine();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            String time = scanner.nextLine();
            String[] parts = time.split(":");
            int hh = Integer.parseInt(parts[0]);
            int mm = Integer.parseInt(parts[1]);

            double hourAngle = (hh % 12) * 30 + mm * 0.5;
            double minuteAngle = mm * 6;
            double angle = Math.abs(hourAngle - minuteAngle);
            angle = Math.min(angle, 360 - angle);

            if (angle >= 0 && angle < 30) {
                System.out.println("alert");
            } else if (angle >= 90 && angle <= 180) {
                System.out.println("safe");
            } else {
                System.out.println("warning");
            }
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class MiddleSquareMethod {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int d = scanner.nextInt();

        for (int x = 1; x <= d; x++) {
            int s = scanner.nextInt();
            System.out.println("Case " + x + ":");

            int current = s;
            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
                long squared = (long) current * current;
                String str = String.format("%08d", squared);
                String middle = str.substring(2, 6);
                current = Integer.parseInt(middle);
                System.out.println(current);
            }
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class CollatzConjecture {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;
            int count = 0;
            while (n != 1) {
                if (n % 2 == 0) {
                    n /= 2;
                } else {
                    n = 3 * n + 1;
                }
                count++;
            }
            System.out.println(count);
        }
        scanner.close();
    }
}

Class 654:   2 fragments, nominal size 25 lines, similarity 100%

train/1/deepseek_p00175_4P.java: 1-28 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == -1) {
                break;
            }
            System.out.println(convertToBase4(n));
        }
        scanner.close();
    }

    private static String convertToBase4(int n) {
        if (n == 0) {
            return "0";
        }
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while (n > 0) {
            sb.insert(0, n % 4);
            n /= 4;
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}

    private static String convertToQuaternary(int n) {
        if (n == 0) {
            return "0";

train/1/deepseek_p00183_2P.java: 1-49 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class TicTacToe {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            String line1 = scanner.nextLine();
            if (line1.equals("0")) {
                break;
            }
            String line2 = scanner.nextLine();
            String line3 = scanner.nextLine();

            char[][] board = new char[3][3];
            board[0] = line1.toCharArray();
            board[1] = line2.toCharArray();
            board[2] = line3.toCharArray();

            String result = checkWinner(board);
            System.out.println(result);
        }
        scanner.close();
    }

    private static String checkWinner(char[][] board) {
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            if (board[i][0] == board[i][1] && board[i][1] == board[i][2]) {
                if (board[i][0] == 'b') return "b";
                if (board[i][0] == 'w') return "w";
            }
        }
        for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
            if (board[0][j] == board[1][j] && board[1][j] == board[2][j]) {
                if (board[0][j] == 'b') return "b";
                if (board[0][j] == 'w') return "w";
            }
        }
        if (board[0][0] == board[1][1] && board[1][1] == board[2][2]) {
            if (board[0][0] == 'b') return "b";
            if (board[0][0] == 'w') return "w";
        }
        if (board[0][2] == board[1][1] && board[1][1] == board[2][0]) {
            if (board[0][2] == 'b') return "b";
            if (board[0][2] == 'w') return "w";
        }
        return "NA";
    }
}

public class TicTacToe {

            board[2] = line3.toCharArray();

            String result = checkWinner(board);
            System.out.println(result);
        }
        scanner.close();
    }

    private static String checkWinner(char[][] board) {
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            if (board[i][0] == board[i][1] && board[i][1] == board[i][2]) {
                if (board[i][0] == 'b') return "b";
                if (board[i][0] == 'w') return "w";
            }

        for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
            if (board[0][j] == board[1][j] && board[1][j] == board[2][j]) {
                if (board[0][j] == 'b') return "b";
                if (board[0][j] == 'w') return "w";
            }
        }

        if (board[0][0] == board[1][1] && board[1][1] == board[2][2]) {

train/1/deepseek_p00188_3P.java: 1-38 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class BinarySearchCount {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            int[] arr = new int[n];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                arr[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            }
            int k = scanner.nextInt();

            int count = 0;
            int left = 0;
            int right = n - 1;

            while (left <= right) {
                count++;
                int mid = (left + right) / 2;

                if (arr[mid] == k) {
                    break;
                } else if (k < arr[mid]) {
                    right = mid - 1;
                } else {
                    left = mid + 1;
                }
            }

            System.out.println(count);
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            if (n == 0) break;

            int[] counts = new int[10];
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int c = scanner.nextInt();
                counts[c]++;
            }

            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
                if (counts[i] == 0) {
                    System.out.println("-");
                } else {
                    System.out.println("*".repeat(counts[i]));
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

train/1/deepseek_p00238_4P.java: 1-27 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class StudyTimeCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        while (true) {
            int t = scanner.nextInt();
            if (t == 0) {
                break;
            }
            int n = scanner.nextInt();
            int total = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int s = scanner.nextInt();
                int f = scanner.nextInt();
                total += (f - s);
            }
            if (total >= t) {
                System.out.println("OK");
            } else {
                System.out.println(t - total);
            }
        }
        scanner.close();
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        while (true) {
            int targetTime = sc.nextInt();
            if (targetTime == 0) {
                break;
            }

            int n = sc.nextInt();
            int totalStudyTime = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int startTime = sc.nextInt();
                int endTime = sc.nextInt();

                System.out.println("OK");
            } else {
                System.out.println(targetTime - totalStudyTime);
            }
        }

        sc.close();
    }

train/1/deepseek_p00436_1P.java: 1-37 
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();
        int[] cards = new int[2 * n];

        for (int i = 0; i < 2 * n; i++) {
            cards[i] = i + 1;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            int k = sc.nextInt();
            if (k == 0) {
                int[] newCards = new int[2 * n];
                int index = 0;
                for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                    newCards[index++] = cards[j];
                    newCards[index++] = cards[j + n];
                }
                cards = newCards;
            } else {
                int[] newCards = new int[2 * n];
                System.arraycopy(cards, k, newCards, 0, 2 * n - k);
                System.arraycopy(cards, 0, newCards, 2 * n - k, k);
                cards = newCards;
            }
        }

        for (int card : cards) {
            System.out.println(card);
        }
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int n = scanner.nextInt();
        int m = scanner.nextInt();
        int[] cards = new int[2 * n];

        for (int i = 0; i < 2 * n; i++) {
            cards[i] = i + 1;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {

            if (k == 0) {
                int[] newCards = new int[2 * n];
                int index = 0;
                for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                    newCards[index++] = cards[j];
                    newCards[index++] = cards[j + n];
                }
                cards = newCards;
            } else {
                int[] newCards = new int[2 * n];
                System.arraycopy(cards, k, newCards, 0, 2 * n - k);
                System.arraycopy(cards, 0, newCards, 2 * n - k, k);
                cards = newCards;
            }
        }

        for (int card : cards) {
            System.out.println(card);
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class TimeCard {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            int sh = scanner.nextInt();
            int sm = scanner.nextInt();
            int ss = scanner.nextInt();
            int eh = scanner.nextInt();
            int em = scanner.nextInt();
            int es = scanner.nextInt();

            int start = sh * 3600 + sm * 60 + ss;
            int end = eh * 3600 + em * 60 + es;
            int diff = end - start;

            int h = diff / 3600;
            int m = (diff % 3600) / 60;
            int s = diff % 60;

            System.out.println(h + " " + m + " " + s);
        }
    }
}

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int[] nums = new int[N];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            nums[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        long[][] dp = new long[N][21];
        dp[0][nums[0]] = 1;

        for (int i = 1; i < N - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= 20; j++) {
                if (dp[i - 1][j] > 0) {
                    int plus = j + nums[i];
                    if (plus <= 20) {
                        dp[i][plus] += dp[i - 1][j];
                    }
                    int minus = j - nums[i];
                    if (minus >= 0) {
                        dp[i][minus] += dp[i - 1][j];
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(dp[N - 2][nums[N - 1]]);
    }
}

            numbers[i] = scanner.nextInt();

        long[][] dp = new long[N][21];
        dp[0][numbers[0]] = 1;

        for (int i = 1; i < N - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= 20; j++) {
                if (dp[i - 1][j] > 0) {
                    int nextAdd = j + numbers[i];
                    if (nextAdd <= 20) {
                        dp[i][nextAdd] += dp[i - 1][j];
                    }
                    int nextSub = j - numbers[i];
                    if (nextSub >= 0) {
                        dp[i][nextSub] += dp[i - 1][j];
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(dp[N - 2][numbers[N - 1]]);
    }

train/1/deepseek_p00489_0P.java: 1-57 
import java.util.*;

public class Soccer {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int matches = N * (N - 1) / 2;
        int[] points = new int[N + 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < matches; i++) {
            int A = sc.nextInt();
            int B = sc.nextInt();
            int C = sc.nextInt();
            int D = sc.nextInt();

            if (C > D) {
                points[A] += 3;
            } else if (C < D) {
                points[B] += 3;
            } else {
                points[A] += 1;
                points[B] += 1;
            }
        }

        List<Team> teams = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            teams.add(new Team(i, points[i]));
        }

        Collections.sort(teams, (a, b) -> b.points - a.points);

        int[] ranks = new int[N + 1];
        int rank = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < teams.size(); i++) {
            if (i > 0 && teams.get(i).points != teams.get(i - 1).points) {
                rank = i + 1;
            }
            ranks[teams.get(i).id] = rank;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            System.out.println(ranks[i]);
        }
    }

    static class Team {
        int id;
        int points;

        Team(int id, int points) {
            this.id = id;
            this.points = points;
        }
    }
}

public class Main {

        int matches = N * (N - 1) / 2;

            int B = scanner.nextInt();
            int C = scanner.nextInt();
            int D = scanner.nextInt();

                points[A] += 3;
            } else if (C < D) {
                points[B] += 3;
            } else {
                points[A] += 1;
                points[B] += 1;
            }
        }

        List<Team> teams = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            teams.add(new Team(i, points[i]));
        }

        Collections.sort(teams, (t1, t2) -> t2.points - t1.points);

        int[] ranks = new int[N + 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < teams.size(); i++) {
            if (i > 0 && teams.get(i).points != teams.get(i - 1).points) {
                rank = i + 1;
            }
            ranks[teams.get(i).id] = rank;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            System.out.println(ranks[i]);
        }
    }

    static class Team {
        int id;
        int points;

        Team(int id, int points) {
            this.id = id;
            this.points = points;
        }
    }

train/1/deepseek_p00517_1P.java: 1-32 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class SuperMetropolis {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        int W = scanner.nextInt();
        int H = scanner.nextInt();
        int N = scanner.nextInt();
        int[] X = new int[N];
        int[] Y = new int[N];

        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            X[i] = scanner.nextInt();
            Y[i] = scanner.nextInt();
        }

        int total = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
            int dx = X[i] - X[i-1];
            int dy = Y[i] - Y[i-1];

            if ((dx >= 0 && dy >= 0) || (dx <= 0 && dy <= 0)) {
                total += Math.max(Math.abs(dx), Math.abs(dy));
            } else {
                total += Math.abs(dx) + Math.abs(dy);
            }
        }

        System.out.println(total);
    }
}
